\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f5\fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0 All damage taken during psionic combat is in the form of temporary ability damage. The specific attack mode used dete
rmines the type of temporary ability damage dealt. Temporary ability damage returns naturally at a rate of 1 point per day for each damaged ability (2 points per day under the care of someone versed in the Heal skill). 
\par If a psionic being\rquote s score in any on
e ability damaged by an attack mode reaches 0, he or she drops helpless. All further psionic attacks against that target deal temporary Constitution damage. The downed being cannot raise psionic defenses against these attacks. If his or her Constitution r
eaches 0, he or she immediately dies. If brought back to life through magical or psionic means, the victim comes back with a Constitution score of 1. Lost ability points continue to return normally as the temporary damage fades.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \i\f5\fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0 Psionic Attack and Defense Modes
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f5\fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0 
Psionic attack and defense modes are in many ways akin to standard powers, but they differ in some ways. Since they do not really belong to any one discipline, a psionic character can use any mode he or she has access to without worrying about a key 
ability score.  Psionic attack and defense modes are supernatural, not spell-like.  Using an attack mode draws an attack of opportunity, but using a defense mode does not.
\par 
